Data: 7.10pm Australia have won the toss and will bat, George Bailey is grinning again, as he does. Australia have made two changes, with Chris Lynn, er, rested and Josh Hazlewood dropping out for Daniel Christian and Ben Cutting. England also make two changes, Jordan replacing James Tredwell and Ben Stokes in for Michael Lumb, with Luke Wri
Broad to White, no run slightly back of a length, around the line of off, White goes back and across and defends with a straight bat
Broad to White, no run shortish, touch more width, White jabs at it and squirts the ball in front of point, Morgan stops it well to prevent one
Broad to White, 1 run cross-seam delivery from Broad, Finch pushes it on the full wide of short extra cover for a single
Broad to Finch, 1 run on the stumps, worked back past the bowler, mid-on moves across to his left
Broad to White, 1 run on the stumps, worked off the legs through square
Broad to Finch, no run good length, outside the line and Finch guides it into the covers
Jordan to White, 1 wide and he starts with a wide, firing this narrowly down the leg side
Jordan to White, no run pitched up, wide enough to get White's dander up, but he miscues and thick inside edge into his pads
Jordan to White, no run angled in, slightly full again, clipped firmly to leg where Bresnan makes a diving stop at midwicket
Jordan to White, 2 runs on the stumps and flicked behind square this time, Dernbach makes a bit of a meal of stopping it at fine leg
Jordan to White, 1 run digs this in short and White takes it on, pulling aerially down towards Dernbach, who can't make up the ground and settles for making a goalie stop on the bounce
Jordan to Finch, no run length ball, nips back a touch and rattles into the pads, might have been some bat involved, height an issue too
Jordan to Finch, no run Finch backs away and Jordan follows him, sends a length ball zipping through past a swing and a miss - decent first over from Jordan
Broad to White, no run length ball, tight line around off, tapped short on the off side

Broad to White, FOUR runs you beauty! That's a shot from White, driven crisply, furiously even, on the up and straight back past Broad for the first boundary. Wasn't overpitched but took some punishment
Broad to White, FOUR runs goes again, this time on the pull, Broad dropping short and being carted high over midwicket - he's up and running now
Broad to White, 1 run length in the channel, stays back and opens the face to run one to third man
Broad to Finch, 1 run punches a length ball down the ground, just one as mid-on and mid-off converge
Broad to White, no run ripper from Broad, beats the batsman for pace as the ball zips through off the pitch
Jordan to Finch, FOUR runs Jordan tries the chin music on Finch, whose swats it away at chest height, loopy pull shot but it bounces away to the rope
Jordan to Finch, no run this was slightly more ungainly (less gainly?), as Finch makes room and swings wildly at a short ball that bounces over the stumps
Jordan to Finch, 1 run short and at the batsman, pulled flat through midwicket, there's a fielder out there now
Jordan to White, no run down the leg side, there's a scrape of something - most likely pad - and Buttler then takes a terrific low catch diving to his left. Saved a leg bye, he did
Jordan to White, 1 leg bye fires the ball in full at White's feet as he wanders to leg, deflects away square
Jordan to Finch, 1 run full, attempted yorker, nearly catches Finch out, he swipes an inside edge to deep square leg
Bresnan to Finch, no run good length on the stumps, blocked watchfully

Bresnan to Finch, 1 run pulled, not out of the middle, straight to midwicket but dropped by Jordan! Maybe I spoke too soon... It flew fairly quickly, such is Finch's power, but should have been taken, around head height
Bresnan to White, no run seams back a touch and cramps Whites for room, hitting him near the bread basket
Bresnan to White, no run on the stumps, worked back on the leg side, Jordan scampers in to field
Bresnan to White, 1 run tight line outside off from Bresnan, an inside edge bobbles short on the off side and they get one
Bresnan to Finch, 1 run opens the face and runs a single to short third man
Stokes to Finch, no run starts well, length ball on off stump, tapped into the off side

Stokes to Finch, SIX runs clubbed over deep backward square, that's a monstrous flick from Finch, the first six of the innings! He came forward out of the crease, made the delivery a half-volley on his pads, but the nonchalance with which he launched the ball over the rope was astounding
Stokes to Finch, 2 runs on leg stump, worked through square leg for a couple more
Stokes to Finch, no run good pace, around off stump, Finch has a big old ballyhoo and fails to connect
Stokes to Finch, SIX runs six more, into the crowd at long-on! Overptiched from Stokes and he's taken downtown by the little big man again, crrrrrrrrrrrrunched back over his head
Stokes to Finch, no run shortens his length wisely, outside off, guides the ball straight to short third man
Bresnan to White, 1 run length outside off, White attacks but can't replicate Finch's hitting, skewing a thick edge to third man on the bounce

Bresnan to Finch, SIX runs here goes Finch again - he loves playing against England - carting a slightly fill ball out towards wide long-on, Hales gets round to it but appeared uncertain where the boundary was and compounds his drop but sending it beyond the rope. Tough but takeable
Bresnan to Finch, no run on the stumps, played respectfully back this time

Bresnan to Finch, OUT on the attack, doesn't get hold of a pull and plops the ball to mid-on! England have got their aggressor, Bresnan winkles him out with a half-tracker, miscalculation from Finch, who tried to pull from outside off, maybe wasn't quite short enough either and spooned to the fielder
Bresnan to Maxwell, 1 run full and down the leg side, squirts it through square leg to get off the mark
Bresnan to White, 1 run tight stuff from Bresnan, on off stump and tickled down the ground for one more
Stokes to White, no run good length outside off, White swings and misses
Stokes to White, 1 run low full toss on the stumps, clipped low through the leg side to deep midwicket
Stokes to Maxwell, no run pitched up wide of the wicket, Maxwell fiddles at it and fails to connect
Stokes to Maxwell, 1 wide spears this down the leg side - wide
Stokes to Maxwell, SIX runs brutal, Maxwell smears a flat six over wide long-off! Maybe a touch full from Stokes and Maxwell backed away to smoke it into the crowd
Stokes to Maxwell, no run takes the pace off and the ball bounces over the stumps as Maxwell walks across and attempts a cute dab behind square
Stokes to Maxwell, 1 run back of a length, outside off, smacked down the ground with a baseball slug but straight to long-on
Broad to Maxwell, SIX runs boom, six more! Broad goes short and follows Maxwell, who simply roundhouses it on its way over deep backward square

Broad to Maxwell, OUT swings again but Maxwell has holed out to long-on! The ball was back of a length, Maxwell tried to cross-batter it again, came high off the bat and straight to the man running in from the fence. Another frenzied failure from Maxwell
Broad to White, 1 run leg-stump line, closes the face and works one to backward square leg
Broad to Cutting, 2 runs goes back and runs a couple down to third man
Broad to Cutting, no run tries to dab the ball to the same part of the ground and it's cut off on the edge of the ring, Lumb the substitute, he has a shy with Cutting stranded but fails to hit!
Broad to Cutting, SIX runs launches into a length ball and sends it high, high, high and just beyond the boundary at long-on. Told you
Dernbach to White, no run starts with a length ball on the stumps, White gets behind the line
Dernbach to White, 2 runs fuller, in the channel, driven through the covers for a couple into the deep
Dernbach to White, no run good line, White pushes into the off side, cut off in the circle
Dernbach to White, 1 run now the slower ball from Dernbach, out the back of the hand, White watches it on to the bat around leg stump and steers one through square
Dernbach to Cutting, 1 run length ball outside the line of off, opens the face and guides one to third man
Dernbach to White, 1 run full and straight, right up in the blockhole, White bunts one to long-on - not bad, Jade, not bad
Bresnan to White, FOUR runs full ball on the stumps, swung into the leg side, powerful strike and runs to the fence
Bresnan to White, FOUR runs slower ball on leg stump, flicked very fine and it skips away for four more
Bresnan to White, 1 run Bresnan drags his length back and gets punched down to long-on
Bresnan to Cutting, SIX runs length ball and heaved over the longest part of the ground, big smash right across the line and nailed it into the stands
Bresnan to Cutting, 2 runs lovely timed straight drive but it cannons the bowler's end stumps and ricochets into midwicket for a couple
Bresnan to Cutting, 1 run excellent yorker, dug out down to long-off
Dernbach to Cutting, 1 run short ball pulled out to deep midwicket
Dernbach to White, 1 run length delivery, slower ball on the stumps, turned carefully to the leg side 45 and they get a quick single
Dernbach to Cutting, 1 wide full but well wide of off stump, 100 up
Dernbach to Cutting, no run excellent quick yorker and Cutting is hurried into digging out the toe-crusher
Dernbach to Cutting, FOUR runs full length swung hard down the ground, Root sliding to his left at long-on misses, perhaps could have done better there
Dernbach to Cutting, no run slower ball on leg stump and Cutting seems to nudge around the corner but ends up shovelling it off his elbow to the 45
Dernbach to Cutting, no run full outside off, big swing and a miss
Jordan to Bailey, 1 run short ball, swatted down into midwicket and it's just a single, exactly what England wanted
Jordan to Wade, 1 run full on leg stump, flicked down to long leg
Jordan to Bailey, 2 runs turned into square leg, they sprint hard for two and the throw from Stokes is miles off line so they get home safe as houses
Jordan to Bailey, 1 run full on off stump, knocked into the covers and they get an easy run
Jordan to Wade, 1 run full on the stumps, turned into the leg side and there's another easy single
Jordan to Bailey, 1 run very full, excellent delivery, turned down to long leg for an easy single
Dernbach to Bailey, 1 run bumper, gets up well over Bailey's head, he uppercuts it down to third man on the bounce
Dernbach to Wade, 1 run good length, Wade is forward and knocks it into point
Dernbach to Bailey, 1 run full angled in, Bailey steps to leg and pushes into the covers
Dernbach to Wade, 1 wide wide, well down leg

Dernbach to Wade, 2 runs slower ball on the stumps, slogged straight up in the air, it goes miles up and Bopara is the man running in from deep midwicket, he makes the ground but drops the catch with the ball swirling to his right at the last moment, very tough chance
Dernbach to Wade, FOUR runs short at the body and hammered behind square, nailed the pull
Dernbach to Wade, 1 run another pull, this straight to Bopara again but on the bounce
Stokes to White, SIX runs length on the stumps, White clears the front leg and extends the arms through the shot, creaming it over long-off
Stokes to White, no run forward and angling to short third man, too quickly for a single
Stokes to White, 1 run full length angled in, pushed firmly down to long-off
Stokes to Cutting, no run length ball, Cutting opens up to swing it to leg but misses
Stokes to Cutting, SIX runs full on the stumps, another lovely swing down the ground, clears long-off this time, managed to play it inside out against the angle, sweetly timed
Stokes to Cutting, no run back of a length, goes to uppercut but misses completely
Root to White, 1 run around the wicket, flicked out to deep midwicket for an easy single

Root to Cutting, OUT down the track, punches firmly back towards the bowler but Root reaches out to his left and clings onto a rifling chance that was struck very well but evidently too straight and Root intervened to perfect effect
Root to Bailey, no run down the track, goes to flick to leg but gets struck on the thigh pad
Root to Bailey, FOUR runs another step down the wicket, this time picks it up over the leg side and places it perfectly in between deep midwicket and long-on
Root to Bailey, 2 runs now smashes off side and Jordan has to run to his left to field, does well
Root to Bailey, SIX runs another step down and hits this off a length over long-on, cracking timing again
Bresnan to Wade, SIX runs length ball, slower ball, long ball over midwicket, flat and hard, smashed
Bresnan to Wade, 1 run much fuller and angled to backward point
Bresnan to Bailey, 2 runs full on leg stump, clubbed leg side, Bopara comes in to field but can't save two
Bresnan to Bailey, 1 run short ball, pulled without timing, deep-square is in quickly and saves the second
Bresnan to Wade, no run short and pulled from outside off, except he misses completely
Bresnan to Wade, 2 runs full at leg stump, swung towards deep midwicket and they race back for two
Dernbach to Bailey, FOUR runs short ball outside off and Bailey swings wildly at it, gets it off the toe and finds wide long-on
Dernbach to Bailey, SIX runs slower ball bouncer, Bailey steps back and whacks it mid-off and it clears the rope! Amazing shot, what power
Dernbach to Bailey, SIX runs slower on the stumps, Bailey swings it hard over the leg side and clears the rope again! Slower ball picked up and it has enough length to carry wide long-on
Dernbach to Bailey, FOUR runs full and wide of off stump, Bailey reaches out and hammers this wide of deep cover, that almost carried for six as well
Dernbach to Bailey, FOUR runs length outside off, Bailey swings it away again, this past extra cover and there's enough pace to find the fence again!

Dernbach to Bailey, 2 runs full and wide, Bailey has to almost dive across for it, gets a thick outside edge to third man, Wright saves with super dive and throws back to Buttler who manages to miss the stumps with a flick of the hands meaning Bailey got back for the second

What a final over from Bailey and has taken Australia from what was only a par score to a very good total, England would not have been expecting to chase above 190 when they took a flurry of wickets to reduce Australia to 139 for 6 with four overs to go. But Bailey's blinder puts Australia in the box seat for another win and Monty will
Howdy, back again. That final over may have put a cork in the tour for England. Oh Jade... This will again be a record chase, though it's not above 200, despite George Bailey's best efforts.
Luke Wright is going to face the first ball, he's had a good BBL opening the batting for the Stars. Mitchell Starc has the ball
Starc to Wright, 1 run over the wicket, on a length and there's a hint of inswing as Wright closes the face, works one past midwicket
Starc to Hales, no run again this comes back, Hales is a little stuck in the crease and gets an inside edge on to his pads, the ball just dropping past leg stump
Starc to Hales, no run pitched up in the channel, swings the arms and chops a bump ball into the hands of cover point
Starc to Hales, 1 run full and wide again, steered this time down to third man
Starc to Wright, 2 runs short of a length, on the hips and nurdled behind square for a couple
Starc to Wright, 1 run pitched up around off stump, big backlift from Wright but he doesn't connect cleanly and gets just a single wide of mid-on
Coulter-Nile to Wright, no run length ball in the channel outside off, Wright plays a watchful leave. Lovely
Coulter-Nile to Wright, no run fuller, around off stump, comes forward and taps into the covers
Coulter-Nile to Wright, no run NCN is up at 88mph, tight line in the corridor, Wright steers straight to point from the crease
Coulter-Nile to Wright, no run bit of width, Wright swings hard but fails to connect, might have bounced a tad more than expected

Coulter-Nile to Wright, no run is that a drop? Replays suggest it might have been, Coulter-Nile certainly thinks so, Wade fumbling a low take to his left as Wright got a thin edge down the leg side trying to glance off his hips
Coulter-Nile to Wright, FOUR runs and he cashes that cheque, denying the bowler a maiden with a scooped four down the leg side from a short delivery on the stumps
Starc to Hales, 1 wide fired full and wide of the stumps... too wide
Starc to Hales, no run pitched up, outside the line of off, squeezed to point as Hales chops down on it
Starc to Hales, 1 run goes for the inswinging yorker, gets enough bat on it to squeeze one through backward point
Starc to Wright, no run quick and in the channel outside off, another swing and a miss from Wright
Starc to Wright, no run gets away with a full toss, on the stumps and hacked back down the track, Starc collects in his follow through and the scorers mark a dot

Starc to Wright, OUT drops short, pulled... straight to deep square leg! So Wright gets another single-figure score, despite moving up the order, he was in position to play the shot, went aerial but can't have been looking at the field. Cutting did a two-step to his right and then settled for the take
Starc to Stokes, 4 leg byes full, attempted yorker, I think, slides down the leg side, flick of pad and it beats Wade's dive
Coulter-Nile to Hales, no run slightly short of a length, follows the batsman, who plays it on to his body aiming to leg
Coulter-Nile to Hales, FOUR runs driven on the up just over extra cover, first boundary for Hales, got enough on it and cleared the infield

Coulter-Nile to Hales, OUT now Hales has picked out deep square leg, this time on the run! Sweetly timed, a little pick-up swivel pull, but not enough to clear the boundary, there is only one man out there but he made good ground and England lose both openers in similar fashion
Coulter-Nile to Root, no run shuffles across and plays a length ball into the off side
Coulter-Nile to Root, no run off-stump line from Coulter-Nile, Root again plays watchfully with a straight bat
Coulter-Nile to Root, no run gets across and defends a length ball square on the off side - another cracking over from Coulter-Nile, keeping the pressure on
Maxwell to Stokes, FOUR runs pushed through flat outside off from round the wicket, Stokes makes room to swing a cross-batted drive through the covers for four
Maxwell to Stokes, 1 run angled in, worked wide of mid-on for one
Maxwell to Root, no run flat, on the stumps, turned to midwicket
Maxwell to Root, no run tossed up, pushed back to the bowler's right, Maxwell doesn't completely stop it but mid-on prevents a run
Maxwell to Root, 1 run full and wide of the stumps, Root mows across the line, gets a bottom edge that bounces over the stumps, past Wade for one

Maxwell to Stokes, OUT heave ho, off he goes, a loopy leading edge caught on the edge of the ring! Stokes laid the dynamite but only succeeded in blowing himself up, swinging hard and falling harder, the ball looped towards point and Cutting took an excellent catch back-pedalling
Cutting to Root, no run pitched up outside the line of off, Root chops into the ground towards point
Cutting to Root, no run on the stumps, pushed back on the up to mid-on

Cutting to Root, FOUR runs drags this short and Root plays a orthodox pull, flat and in front of deep midwicket, where Muirhead gets to it on the slide but only manages to flip the ball beyond the rope for four
Cutting to Root, 1 run bit of width, opens the face and steers one to third man
Cutting to Morgan, 1 run length ball on off stump, pushes at it and in inside edge runs short and square on the leg side for one
Cutting to Root, no run goes back and cuts hard, it's stopped well at backward point and then Morgan has to throw himself back to regain his ground at the other end
Maxwell to Morgan, 2 runs darted outside off, comes forward and chips a couple over the infield towards deep extra cover
Maxwell to Morgan, 1 run tossed up and punched down the ground on the front foot
Maxwell to Root, no run floated up on the stumps, Root tries reverse-sweep and is hit on the pad, possibly a little glove saves him, as the umpire turns down Maxwell's appeal
Maxwell to Root, 2 byes full on the stumps, conventional slog-sweep attempted this time and the ball misses everything, they run a couple
Maxwell to Root, 1 run pushed across from round the wicket, runs a single to short third man

Maxwell to Morgan, SIX runs skips forward to a full ball and boings it over wide long-off! Such power in those wrists, the bottom hand coming through as a mere punch soars beyond the boundary for England's first maximum
Christian to Root, no run on the stumps, dabbed into the off side
Christian to Root, 1 run gets forward and pushes this through the covers for a single
Christian to Morgan, SIX runs goes round the wicket, Morgan moves outside the line and plays an audacious scoop over fine leg! Clever batting and that's six more
Christian to Morgan, 1 run goes fuller, still outside off, squeezes one in front of square
Christian to Root, 1 run touch short, Root swats it aggressively down the ground for one
Christian to Morgan, 1 run Morgan leaves the crease and clumps one to long-on for another single

Maxwell to Morgan, FOUR runs oh dear, Cutting has had a mare here, moving round the boundary at deep cover to stop a drive, he slides past it, makes the pick up and then somehow manages to toss it on to the rope, unable to pull it back in slow motion with a groping hand
Maxwell to Morgan, 1 run comes forward again and drills one to long-off
Maxwell to Root, 2 runs pushed through on leg stump, nurdles a couple through backward square
Maxwell to Root, no run on the stumps, sweeps flat but picks out midwicket
Maxwell to Root, no run opens the shoulders, can't force the ball into a gap on the leg side
Cutting to Buttler, no run full and worked to leg, midwicket cuts it off
Cutting to Buttler, no run gets forward and punches a full delivery towards mid-off, turns down a tight single
Cutting to Buttler, 1 run short and at the batsman, who top-edges a pull, into a gap at square leg for one to get Buttler off the mark
Cutting to Morgan, 1 wide short and wide down the leg side as Morgan swings and misses
Cutting to Morgan, 1 run stays back in the crease, settles for a a dabbed single through square
Cutting to Buttler, FOUR runs adroitly done by Buttler, a legcutter from Cutting and he waits on it before flicking a ramped four over the head of Wade. England need a few several lots more of those
Cutting to Buttler, no run tries again, this time scoops and misses
Maxwell to Morgan, FOUR runs tossed up and slapped over the covers for another boundary, Morgan moving smoothly through the gears
Maxwell to Morgan, no run Maxwell scampers to the leg side to field off his own bowling
Maxwell to Morgan, no run on the stumps, played back to the bowler
Maxwell to Morgan, 1 run on the charge, swings and edges but it bounces in front of short third man and Morgan lives
Maxwell to Buttler, 1 run comes forward and punches a single to long-off
Maxwell to Morgan, 2 runs flat, worked into the leg side and they want two, Maxwell again chases after it but Morgan makes it home, good running
Christian to Buttler, 1 run length on off stump, worked into midwicket, just for a single
Christian to Morgan, 1 run length outside off, slapped down to long-off
Christian to Buttler, 1 run slower ball, back of a length on off stump, Buttler heaves it down to long-off
Christian to Morgan, no run full, angled in, Morgan tucked up and struck on the pad which runs towards cover and the bowler fields
Christian to Morgan, 1 run Morgan steps to leg, Christian follows him and Morgan flicks it around the corner for a single
Cutting to Bopara, 1 run length on the stumps, flicked through square leg and the fielder races in to save the second
Cutting to Morgan, 1 run pulled without timing down to long leg
Cutting to Bopara, 1 run Bapara steps back and flicks from off stump to short third man

Cutting to Morgan, OUT length ball swung to leg, Morgan doesn't get all of this, in comes Starc from deep square leg, dives forward and takes the catch but of course when it's close, which this is, they will go upstairs to have a check and there's every chance this could be overturned but thankfully not because the catch looked
Cutting to Bresnan, 1 run short and pulled off the splice of the bat, no-one at square leg so gets away with this for a single
Cutting to Bopara, 1 run short again, better pull but straight to deep-square
Coulter-Nile to Bopara, 1 run excellent yorker dug out into the covers
Coulter-Nile to Bresnan, 2 runs clears the front leg and swings backward of square, there's a fumble and they get back for two
Coulter-Nile to Bresnan, FOUR runs length ball struck frimly wide of long-on and Finch simply can't be bothered running to his right, a lazy one hand and he misses the ball completely
Coulter-Nile to Bresnan, 1 run huge swing and a thick inside edge to long leg

Coulter-Nile to Bopara, OUT huge swing at a full ball, gets a huge inside edge into his pad and it trickles slowly into leg stump and that is a very unfortunate way to go. The ball cannoned of the inside of his pad and agonisingly rolled steadily towards the stumps, glanced the base of the leg stick and off dropped the bail
Coulter-Nile to Jordan, no run blocked on the back foot in front of off stump
Muirhead to Bresnan, no run tossed up, Bresnan ends up trying to late cut off the stumps and almost misses, gets a bottom edge to slip on the bounce
Muirhead to Bresnan, SIX runs nice stride down the wicket and hammered down the ground, strong shot

Muirhead to Bresnan, OUT swing outside off, misses courtesy of the turn, Wade has the bails off and there's a strong appeal for a stumping and Wade was sharp to remove the bails as Bresnan dragged his bag foot a good two inches out of his ground and fails to get back in time
Muirhead to Broad, no run tries to paddle sweep from outside off and misses
Muirhead to Broad, 1 run shorter, flicked around the corner to deep-backward square who's very fine
Muirhead to Jordan, no run floated up on off stump, driven off a thick outside edge to backward point
Coulter-Nile to Broad, 1 run back of a length, angled to backward point and they get a sharp single
Coulter-Nile to Jordan, no run bumper, well-directed, Jordan misses with a hook
Coulter-Nile to Jordan, no run full angled in, Jordan gets struck on the pad squared up
Coulter-Nile to Jordan, no run full and swung, missed completely, it goes past leg stump
Coulter-Nile to Jordan, FOUR runs short and gets a bat on this, manages to get it backward of square and finds the gap
Coulter-Nile to Jordan, no run swing and a miss at a full ball again, it grazes leg stump again
Muirhead to Dernbach, no run back to cut or pull or smash it anywhere, he missed
Muirhead to Dernbach, 1 run full toss outside off, smashed almost to mid-on, it just doesn't carry
Muirhead to Jordan, FOUR runs floated up outside off, driven nicely on the up and gets it wide of mid-off, well timed
Muirhead to Jordan, no run turn away from off stump, swung at, hit on the toe into the covers
Muirhead to Jordan, 1 run swung from off stump, it whirls off a thick outside edge towards deep point
Starc to Jordan, no run full at the stumps, aims leg side and gets a thick edge into his pad

Starc to Jordan, 1 run, OUT short outside off, pulled into midwicket, Dernbach wants to come back for two, whoopsie! It's never on and he's run out by a street trying to scramble back to the striker's end and that's a calamitous end to a truly horrendous tour for England

All over, it had been all over for a long time really, Australia win by 84 runs which is a colossal margin in a T20. It wraps up a 3-0 victory in this series and completes a 12-1 annihilation for England on this trip which has been as miserable as a grey afternoon in Barnsley. Oh goodness have England been pathetic but at least it's al

Today, England were doing quite well with a run of wickets but not for the first time the decent position was whipped from them. George Bailey did the damage in a final over spanking of Jade Dernbach and England were never going to chase 196 and never got in the game second innings.

Right, at long last this series is over and may Australia and England not play each other for a very long time! We've had enough fixtures to last a lifetime in this past eight months. But both teams are in action again pretty soon with Australia travelling to South Africa for a mouthwatering Test series and England back in action at th
Australia won by 84 runs
Player of the match is George Bailey, AUS
